                                         "PostMention":  ""
                                     },
                                     {
                                         "text":  "#### GuthÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€ Ã¢â‚¬â„¢ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¬ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¾ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢s solution\n\nDoctor Alan Guth proposed a solution to this problem. At the beginning of the universe, when matter and energy were still unified, there was a monumental expansion in an extremely short period of time ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€ Ã¢â‚¬â„¢ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¬ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¬ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â the universe grew in size extremely fast (exponential).\n\nThus, although the opposite ends have not been in contact for billions of years, there was a time when the universe was homogeneous, and that homogeneity remained after its exponential expansion (<htcite0>; <htcite1>).\n\n#### Is there proof?\n\nScience is not made up solely of theories; many ideas are refined to reach a deeper understanding. The same applies to the Inflation Theory, as Doctor Guth himself acknowledged and Doctor Lincoln explained in his video (<htcite2>; <htcite3>).\n\nSome experiments suggest that inflation did in fact occur, while others highlight the need for more evidence and further research.",
